<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<chapter version="5.0"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook http://www.docbook.org/xml/5.0/xsd/docbook.xsd"
    xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
    xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mth="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"
    xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="favorites">
    <section>
        <section>
            <title>Manage
                <?oxy_comment_start author="rachaelb" timestamp="20161010T225935+0200" comment="Can you import favorites/export from or to say an Excel spreadsheet? A bulk operation so to speak? Any limitations if doable?

Are favorites language-specific? Can I import from French for example? Is this supported?"?>favorites<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
         <para>You can view the details and interpretations of your favorites when you open the
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="rachaelb" timestamp="20161010T224006+0200" comment="Check/enumerate any other apps that are concerned besides the pivot table and data viz apps."?><emphasis
                    role="bold">Pivot table</emphasis> or <emphasis role="bold">Data
                    Visualization</emphasis> app<?oxy_comment_end?>. You can edit descriptions,
                share your favorites, or write interpretations directly in this pane, or you can use
                the <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> menu.</para>
            <section>
                <title>Open a favorite</title>
                <orderedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                            >Open</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Search for favorites by entering the name of the favorite in the
                            search field, or use <emphasis role="bold">Prev</emphasis> and <emphasis
                                role="bold">Next</emphasis> to display favorites.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </orderedlist>
            </section>
            <section>
                <title>Save a favorite</title>
                <orderedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">Save
                            as</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Enter a name, title and description for your favorite.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </orderedlist>
            </section>
            <section>
                <title>Rename a favorite</title>
                <orderedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                            >Rename</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Enter the new name for your favorite.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Rename</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </orderedlist>
            </section>
            <section>
                <title>Write an interpretation for a favorite</title>
                <para role="">An interpretation is a link to a resource with a description of the
                    data. You can share this information with other people.</para>
                <orderedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">Write
                            interpretation</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><?oxy_comment_start author="rachaelb" timestamp="20161010T224321+0200" comment="Is there a set length of characters or any other criteria such as support /non-support of certain characters etc?"?>In
                            the text field, type a comment, question or
                            interpretation.<?oxy_comment_end?> You can see this information on the
                                <emphasis role="bold">dashboard</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Add a user group that you want to share your favorite with by clicking
                            the <emphasis role="bold">+</emphasis> icon.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><?oxy_comment_start author="rachaelb" timestamp="20161010T225040+0200" comment="Check what the workflow is here with Jan Helge"?>Select:<?oxy_comment_end?><orderedlist>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para><emphasis role="bold"
                                            ><?oxy_comment_start author="rachaelb" timestamp="20161010T154603+0200" comment="Continue updating text here based on recent UI"?>Allow
                                            external access</emphasis> if you want people outside of
                                        your organisation or user group to view this
                                        interpretation.<?oxy_comment_end?></para>
                                </listitem>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para><emphasis role="bold">Public access</emphasis></para>
                                </listitem>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para><emphasis role="bold">Administrators</emphasis></para>
                                </listitem>
                            </orderedlist></para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Share</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </orderedlist>
            </section>
           
            <section>
                <title>Create a link to a favorite</title>
                <para>
                    <orderedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">Get
                                link</emphasis>.</para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Choose one of the following:</para>
                            <itemizedlist>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para><emphasis role="bold">Open in this app</emphasis>: You get
                                        a URL for the favorite which you can share with other users
                                        by email or chat.</para>
                                </listitem>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para><emphasis role="bold">Open in web api</emphasis>: You get
                                        a URL of the API resource. By default this is an HTML
                                        resource, but you can change the file extension to
                                        &quot;.json&quot; or &quot;.csv&quot;.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </itemizedlist>
                        </listitem>
                    </orderedlist>
                </para>
            </section>
            <section>
                <title>Delete a favorite</title>
                <para>
                    <orderedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            <para><?oxy_comment_start author="rachaelb" timestamp="20161010T225737+0200" comment="Does this only apply to a favorite in one app? Can favorites be shared across apps? If yes, does this have an effect if you delete a favorite in one place? What happens?"?>Click
                                    <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis
                                    role="bold">Delete</emphasis><?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Delete</emphasis> to confirm your choice.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </orderedlist>
                </para>
            </section>
        </section>
    </section>
</chapter>
